This paper is likely to belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and computer vision (cs.CV) sub-categories as it deals with deep neural networks and their compression after domain transfer. It also involves artificial intelligence (cs.AI) as it aims to optimize the network for a specific target domain. Additionally, it may fall under the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) and multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories as it deals with neural networks and their application in image and video processing.
